Author: Cryptofist#7504
Content:
Hi I'm working on adding the "What is proof of Gameplay?" section  to the ANN now.
``what rogue CC uses is the actual gameplay keystrokes, it is pretty direct and literal proof of gameplay``
What does RogueCC use the gameplay keystrokes for specifically? Any other tidbits that should go here to inform users of PoG ?

Author: gcharang#6833
Content: RogueCC rewards coins for submitting verifiable proof of game play with some limitations. like dead characters don't get ROGUE etc.,

Author: Cryptofist#7504
Content: Thank you @gcharang , I had "uses the keystrokes to convert game gold to ROGUE" but didnt think that was right, this helps a lot thank you!

Author: gt#2812
Content: i was under the impression that ‚Äúproof of gameplay‚Äù is showing that you‚Äôve put in time (via playing via keystrokes etc) to be rewarded with gold which can than be exchanged for rogue coins

Author: Cryptofist#7504
Content: ``Rogue CC rewards ROGUE to players by verifying the gameplay keystrokes, it quite literally is Proof of Gameplay. ``

Author: gcharang#6833
Content: And that happens when a character bailsout or wins, gold collected is converted to ROGUE in a pre-determined ratio for different modes

Author: Cryptofist#7504
Content: On bailout (quiting while alive) the game automataically converts your in game gold to ROGUE

Author: Cryptofist#7504
Content: Now that part I DO know. üòÉ
